        "title": "refactor(memory-core): split dreaming-phases.ts into 3 focused files",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nSplit the 1828-line `dreaming-phases.ts` into three focused modules:\n\n| File | Lines | Purpose |\n|------|-------|---------|\n| `dreaming-shared-types.ts` | 428 | Shared types, constants, normalize utils |\n| `dreaming-session-corpus.ts` | 646 | Session transcript scanning logic |\n| `dreaming-phases.ts` | 983 | Daily ingestion + phase runners + sweep |\n\n**No runtime behavior changes** — purely a structural refactor.\n\n## Why\nThe original `dreaming-phases.ts` was a 58KB single file (1828 lines) handling daily file scanning, session transcript corpus scanning, state normalization, REM/Light dreaming phase logic, and sweep orchestration. This made it the primary maintainability hazard in the memory-core plugin.\n\n## Files\n- `dreaming-phases.ts` — rewritten (1828→983 lines)\n- `dreaming-session-corpus.ts` — **new** (646 lines)\n- `dreaming-shared-types.ts` — **new** (428 lines)",
